article.headline: Kahleah Copper scores 34, including late 3-pointer, as Mercury beat Wings 102-96
article.description: — Kahleah Copper scored 34 points, including a late 3-pointer, and Brittney Griner added 24 points to help the Phoenix Mercury beat the Dallas Wings 104-96 Wednesday night.
article.linkText: Kahleah Copper scores 34, including late 3-pointer, as Mercury beat Wings 102-96

images.name: Kahleah Copper knocks down 3-pointer in final minute
images.caption: Diana Taurasi finds Kahleah Copper for an open 3-pointer to extend the Mercury's lead over the Wings in the final minute.

article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- — Kahleah Copper scored 34 points, including a late 3-pointer, and Brittney Griner added 24 points to help the Phoenix Mercury beat the Dallas Wings 104-96 Wednesday night. Phoenix was up 61-43 early in the third quarter after a three-point play by Griner before Dallas got to within 99-96 on two free throws by Arike Ogunbowale with 1:54 left. Those would be the last points the Wings would score as Dallas missed two shots over the next 80 seconds. Copper then sealed the win hitting a 3-pointer with 23 seconds left. Diana Taurasi finished with 16 points and Rebecca Allen scored 14 for Phoenix (10-10). Natasha Cloud added 10 points and 10 assists. Natasha Howard scored 14 of her career-high 36 points in the third quarter — and the Wings scored 33 points, their highest-scoring quarter this season as they trimmed the 18-point deficit. Dallas (4-16) has dropped 14 of its past 15 games. Ogunbowale scored 26 points for the Wings and Odyssey Sims added 14. The 32-year-old Howard made 11 of 15 from the field, 13 of 17 from the free-throw line and grabbed 11 rebounds. Dallas won 107-92 in Phoenix on May 25, while the Mercury outlasted the Wings in a 97-90 double-overtime road victory on June 9. The Mercury, who had dropped back-to-back games and three of their past four, have played four games in the past six days. ------ AP WNBA: https://apnews.com/hub/wnba-basketball
